data.title: Photo: 2006 COMMONWEALTH GAMES RHYTHMIC GYMNASTICS
data.meta_description: Canadian gymnast Alexandra Orlando performs her ribbon routine in the rhythmic apparatus finals of the XVIII Commonwealth Games in Melbourne, Australia on March 26, 2006. Orlando, 19, of Toronto, won her sixth gold medal with a score of 13.775 points ahead of Yana Tsikaridze of Montrea and Durratun Rosli of Malaysia. Orlando's six gold medals is the most won by a gymnast at a Commonwealth Games.  (UPI Photo/Grace Chiu).
